description: Campaigning for the Maharashtra and Jharkhand assembly elections concluded on Monday, with both BJP and Congress vying for victory in these crucial polls. The BJP is aiming to retain Maharashtra through its alliance, while the Congress-led opposition seeks to capitalize on its recent Lok Sabha performance. The outcome will significantly impact the political landscape and future trajectories of both parties.
title: Campaign ends in Maharashtra, Jharkhand; Results set to shape NDA, INDIA bloc narratives
Gandhis fixated on 'tijori', looted India's treasury for years: BJP

description: The Election Commission has given the BJP and Congress another week to respond to complaints about their leaders' statements during the election campaign. The complaints allege violations of the poll code.  The parties had requested more time due to their focus on Assembly elections. The deadline extension means any action will come after the elections conclude.
title: EC gives BJP, Congress time till Nov 25 to reply to complaints

description: Rahul Gandhi, during a press conference, accused the Modi government of favoring Gautam Adani by transferring Dharavi land worth Rs one lakh crore. Gandhi claimed that major projects have been shifted from Maharashtra to Gujarat, questioning the tendering process and highlighting the impact on the state's economy.
title: Rahul Gandhi: ‘Ek hain to safe hain’ coined for Modi-Adani duo

description: At the G20 summit in Rio, Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi expressed his support for Brazil's proposal to establish a 'Global Alliance Against Hunger and Poverty.' Modi emphasized the disproportionate impact of food, fuel, and fertilizer shortages on developing nations and highlighted India's commitment to global food security and poverty reduction.
title: G20 will work to reform global institutions: PM Modi

description: Anmol Bishnoi, the brother of gangster Lawrence Bishnoi and a suspect in multiple high-profile cases, has been detained in Sacramento, US. Accused of crimes including the murder of Baba Siddique and involvement in the shooting outside Salman Khan's residence, Bishnoi is also suspected of providing support in the murder of Sidhu Moosewala.
title: Anmol, brother of Lawrence Bishnoi, detained in US

description: Uttar Pradesh Governor Anandiben Patel, speaking at a convocation ceremony, emphasized the importance of recognizing ancient Indian technological advancements. She cited examples like the Pushpak Viman from Ramayana and Rishi Bharadwaj's supposed flight, claiming they predate modern inventions. Patel also presented a unique interpretation of Kumbhakarna, portraying him as a secretive weapons developer rather than a lazy giant.
title: Rishi Bhardwaj built 1st plane, flew over Chowpatty: UP governor

description: The Supreme Court directed Delhi and neighboring states to implement strict pollution control measures as air quality reached alarming levels. The court ordered schools to consider closure, encouraged work-from-home arrangements, and criticized authorities for their delayed response to the crisis.
title: Delhi's 2nd-worst air day on record, SC says Grap-4 to go on till further orders

description: Muslim leaders urged the Muslim community to vote for the opposition Maha Vikas Aghadi (MVA) alliance, sparking controversy and drawing criticism from Hindu religious leaders.  Hindu seers are advocating for Hindu unity and support for the ruling BJP party, framing it as a matter of cultural preservation. The situation highlights the growing religious polarization in Indian politics.
title: Hindu seers oppose Ulema appeal, endorse 'ek hai...' call

description: President Droupadi Murmu has appointed K Sanjay Murthy, the current higher education secretary, as the new Comptroller and Auditor General. Murthy, a 1989-batch IAS officer, will succeed G C Murmu, who is retiring. With extensive administrative experience, Murthy has held positions in various ministries, including Information and Broadcasting, Housing and Urban Affairs, and Commerce and Industry.
title: K Sanjay Murthy appointed next Comptroller and Auditor General

description: Election-related seizures in Maharashtra and Jharkhand have exceeded Rs 1,000 crore, a sevenfold increase from the 2019 assembly polls. The Election Commission reported that the majority of the seizures were in freebies, precious metals, and cash, highlighting attempts to influence voters through illicit means.
title: Value of seizures in Maha, J'khand polls, bypolls breach Rs 1k-crore mark
15 seniors arrested for MBBS student’s death in Patan

description: The Supreme Court reprimanded the Karnataka government for challenging a high court decision that increased compensation for farmers whose land was acquired for an irrigation project. The court emphasized the plight of farmers in the state, where thousands die by suicide annually, and dismissed the government's appeal, stating that farmers deserve fair compensation for their acquired land.
title: Farmers in distress, allow them to survive, SC tells Karnataka

description: Indian Army chief General Upendra Dwivedi is set for a four-day visit to Nepal to bolster bilateral military ties.  The visit comes amid Nepal's refusal to allow its youth into the Indian Army under the Agnipath scheme and growing Chinese influence in the region.
title: Agnipath shadow over Army chief's visit to Nepal

description: During a press conference in Ranchi, Congress leader Rahul Gandhi acknowledged that not implementing a caste census in 2011 was a mistake by the UPA government. He emphasized the necessity of a new caste census to guide equitable resource allocation and policy development, contrasting it with the current administration's focus on a select group of capitalists.
title: Not releasing caste survey data in 2011 was UPA mistake: Rahul

description: Former Maharashtra home minister Anil Deshmukh was injured in a stone-throwing attack on his vehicle in Katol. The incident occurred while Deshmukh was returning from campaigning for his son, Salil, an NCP candidate in the assembly elections. Eyewitnesses reported attackers shouting political slogans.
title: Anil Deshmukh injured as car is stoned; 'stunt', says BJP

description: Union minister Piyush Goyal expressed confidence in the Mahayuti alliance's victory in the upcoming Maharashtra elections. He highlighted the alliance's strong track record of delivering development and criticized the opposition's lack of ideological unity. Goyal emphasized the government's commitment to empowering women through initiatives like the Ladli Bahin allowance.
title: People have made up their mind for Mahayuti: Piyush Goyal
CPM: Centre must intervene to end violence
SC collegium picks Madras HC judge as Chief Justice of Manipur HC

description: Congress has criticized Prime Minister Narendra Modi for neglecting Manipur for the past 18 months amidst escalating violence. The party demands that Modi visit the state before the Parliament's winter session or meet with a delegation from Manipur. They are also calling for the resignation of Chief Minister Biren Singh and Home Minister Amit Shah.
title: PM must visit Manipur before Parliament's winter session: Congress

description: The Manipur government has launched an inquiry and suspended an SSP following police firing in Jiribam. Internet bans have been extended, and a curfew remains in effect.  COCOMI, a Meitei civil organization, protested despite the curfew, demanding justice for women and children found dead in Jiribam.
title: Net curbs extended to 7 Manipur districts as protests intensify

description: The Supreme Court has formed a three-member SIT to investigate the sexual assault of a 10-year-old girl in Chennai. The SIT, comprising senior IPS officers, replaces the CBI probe ordered earlier by the Madras High Court. The court emphasized the need for a swift and transparent investigation, directing the SIT to report progress to the High Court weekly.
title: SC forms SIT to probe 'objectively and fairly' Chennai minor's rape
2 students ‘drown’ in water body, their belongings missing

description: The National People's Party (NPP) expressed its willingness to reconsider its decision of withdrawing support from the BJP-led Manipur government if there is a change in the state's leadership. Meghalaya CM and NPP chief Conrad Sangma clarified that the party's decision stemmed from the lack of confidence in Manipur CM Biren Singh's ability to address the ongoing ethnic conflict.
title: Will review withdrawal of support to govt if Manipur CM is changed: NPP's Sangma

description: The Indian Coast Guard rescued seven Indian fishermen who were apprehended by the Pakistan Maritime Security Agency (PMSA) near the maritime boundary. The fishermen were aboard the fishing boat 'Kal Bhairav' which sank after being damaged during the incident. The Coast Guard ship ICGS Agrim intercepted the PMSA ship and negotiated the release of the fishermen.
title: Coast Guard rescues 7 Indian fishermen from Pakistan custody

description: Manipur chief minister N Biren Singh held a meeting with BJP MLAs and NDA allies to address the state's situation following NPP's withdrawal of support.  NPF, with five legislators, pledged continued support to the BJP government, which maintains a majority with NPF, one JDU MLA, and three Independents.
title: Manipur CM holds talks with NDA allies, NPF reaffirms support

description: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) apprehended Taman Singh Sonwani, former Chhattisgarh Public Service Commission chairman, for allegedly accepting a bribe of Rs 45 lakh. The bribe was reportedly paid by Shravan Kumar Goyal, director of Bajrang Power & Ispat Ltd, to secure deputy collector positions for his son and daughter-in-law.
title: Ex-PSC chief of Chhattisgarh arrested in Rs 45 lakh bribe case

description: The government is preparing to introduce legislation during the winter session of Parliament to enable simultaneous elections for Parliament and state assemblies, aiming for implementation in 2029.  This follows the recommendations of a panel led by former President Ram Nath Kovind.  While seeking consensus, the government plans to initiate parliamentary debate on the bills.
title: '1 nation, 1 election' bill likely in winter session

description: The Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanams (TTD) board passed a resolution mandating that all its non-Hindu employees either opt for voluntary retirement or seek a transfer to other government departments. The decision, supported by the TTD Act and Andhra Pradesh Endowments Act, could impact approximately 300 permanent employees out of 7,000.
title: Take VRS or transfer, Tirumala trust tells non-Hindu staffers

description: A Reddit user, currently pursuing her Master's degree in Computer Science, expressed concerns over the high number of Indian students in her program. She questioned the value of their investment, citing a competitive job market and the potential difficulty of securing work visas. She also highlighted cultural differences in classroom behavior.
title: Computer science student in US university warns: Why do Indians ...

description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi addressed the G20 Summit in Rio de Janeiro, emphasizing India's commitment to fighting hunger and poverty. He highlighted India's successful initiatives in poverty reduction, food security, and healthcare, and expressed support for Brazil's proposal to establish a Global Alliance against Hunger and Poverty.
title: 'Keep in mind challenges & priorities of Global South': PM Modi at G20

description: President Joe Biden made a historic visit to the Amazon rainforest, becoming the first sitting US president to do so. During his visit, he pledged $50 million to Brazil's Amazon Fund and delivered a speech emphasizing the importance of combating climate change. However, his departure from the press conference, where he didn't take questions, sparked humorous reactions online.
title: ‘Tarzan Biden wanders off into Amazon rainforest’: Netizens take jibe at US Prez

description: Former Maharashtra Home Minister Anil Deshmukh was injured in a stone-pelting incident while returning from a political meeting in Nagpur district. The attack occurred on the last day of campaigning for the Maharashtra assembly elections. Police are investigating the incident and have not yet identified the assailants. Deshmukh's son, Salil, is contesting the Katol assembly seat in the elections.
title: NCP-SP leader Anil Deshmukh injured after stones pelted at his car

description: India's Gsat-20 communication satellite, designed to boost broadband and in-flight connectivity, was launched aboard a SpaceX Falcon-9 rocket from Florida. The satellite, weighing 4,700kg and built for a 14-year mission, is expected to significantly enhance communication infrastructure across India. This launch marks the first time India has utilized a US rocket for its space program.
title: SpaceX’s Falcon-9 lifts off with India’s Gsat-20 satellite
2 elephants, a calf electrocuted by wire trap in Sambalpur

description: Dilip Joshi, known for his role as Jethalal in the popular sitcom 'Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah,' has refuted recent rumors about a disagreement with the show's producer, Asit Modi. Joshi expressed disappointment over the false reports and emphasized his commitment to the show, dismissing claims of any discord within the team.
title: TMKOC's Dilip Joshi dismisses reports of fight with Producer Asit Kumarr Modi

description: K Sanjay Murthy, an IAS officer, has been appointed as the new Comptroller and Auditor General (CAG) of India, succeeding Girish Chandra Murmu. Murthy, currently serving as the Secretary of the Department of Higher Education, will assume his new role upon taking charge. The President of India made the appointment, exercising the power vested in her by the Constitution.
title: K Sanjay Murthy becomes next Comptroller and Auditor General

description: The Terminator, a 1984 film, became a science-fiction classic. It presented a captivating story and a concerning portrayal of humanity's future with artificial intelligence. The film introduced Skynet, a rogue AI system that triggers nuclear war against humans. The movie combined action with themes of fate, technology, and human resilience.
title: The Terminator: James Cameron’s sci-fi thriller that predicted AI fears 40 years ago

description: India's Competition Commission imposed a $25.6 million fine on Meta Platforms and ordered WhatsApp to stop sharing user data with other Meta companies for advertising for five years. The regulator ruled that WhatsApp's data-sharing policy was anti-competitive and gave users an unfair "take-it-or-leave-it" choice.
title: CCI fines Meta Rs 213 crore over WhatsApp’s 2021 privacy policy update

description: Donald Trump’s proposed Cabinet, dubbed the “MAGAvengers” by Turning Point USA’s Charlie Kirk, features a team of bold and controversial figures. Pete Hegseth, as Secretary of Defense, plans to overhaul military leadership and eliminate DEI programs, focusing on traditional combat standards. Matt Gaetz, as Attorney General, aims to reform the DOJ and address federal “weaponization.” Robert F. Kennedy Jr. will challenge public health norms as Secretary of Health and Human Services, while Tulsi Gabbard, as Director of National Intelligence, promises integrity in intelligence. Elon Musk will lead government efficiency efforts, and JD Vance, as Vice President, reinforces Trump’s appeal to working-class voters.
title: How Donald Trump is assembling the 'The Avengers' to 'save' USA
Will Maharashtra see new political realignments for CM post again?

description: International Men's Day, celebrated annually on November 19th, is a tribute to the men who enrich our lives with their strength, compassion, and unwavering support. It's a day to express gratitude for their contributions as fathers, brothers, husbands, friends, and sons, acknowledging their invaluable role in our lives and society as a whole.
title: Happy International Men’s Day 2024: Top 50 wishes, messages, and quotes

description: The Supreme Court has ordered the closure of schools in Delhi and NCR due to hazardous air pollution levels, directing the enforcement of GRAP Stage IV measures. Schools in Delhi, Haryana, Punjab, and Uttar Pradesh have shifted to online classes or announced holidays to protect students. The court has emphasised the urgent need for coordinated actions from the central and state governments to combat the severe air quality crisis affecting the region.
title: School closure in NCR ordered by SC amid Delhi pollution

description: President-elect Donald Trump has confirmed his administration will enact a mass deportation program targeting 425,000 undocumented immigrants with criminal records. Trump's border czar, Tom Homan, promised swift action, prioritizing public safety and national security.  Despite warnings from activists about potential economic fallout and human cost, the incoming administration appears committed to fulfilling Trump's campaign promise on immigration.
title: 'True!': Trump confirms he will declare national emergency, use military for mass deportation

description: From surprising collaborations and wedding bells to behind-the-scenes drama, we've rounded up the top entertainment stories that are making headlines. Swara Bhasker faces backlash for alleged "double standards" on women’s rights after meeting Maulana Sajjad Nomani, while Aamir Khan opens up to Anees Bazmee about Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 clashing with Singham Again. Adding to the buzz, Rakesh Roshan announces his retirement from directing films. Buckle up for a thrilling look at the top five entertainment stories stealing the spotlight!
title: Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: Checking your phone first thing in the morning might reveal more about your personality than you realize. From impulsivity and fear of missing out to a need for validation and procrastination, your phone habits could be signaling deeper tendencies and potential stressors impacting your well-being.
title: Revealed: The psychology of checking phone soon after waking up

description: Netflix experienced a significant outage during the highly anticipated Mike Tyson vs. Jake Paul fight, preventing thousands of viewers, particularly in the US and India, from watching the event. Despite the technical difficulties, the fight drew a record 60 million viewers globally. The outage sparked widespread frustration and criticism on social media, with many users reporting streaming problems.
title: Mike Tyson vs Jake Paul: Read Netflix's 'acceptance note' on streaming issue

description: The Uttar Pradesh Secondary Education Board has announced the schedule for the 2025 board exams for Class 10 and Class 12 students. Exams for both levels will begin on February 24, 2025, and end on March 12, 2025. Key exams include Hindi, Maths, Science, and Social Studies for Class 10, and Hindi, Civics, Maths, Economics, and History for Class 12. A total of 54.38 million students have registered for the exams, slightly fewer than in 2024.
title: UP board time table 2025 released: Exams to begin on February 24

description: The death toll from a fire incident at Maharani Laxmi Bai Medical College in Jhansi has risen to 12 after another infant succumbed to injuries. 39 infants were rescued from the Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU) during the fire on Friday night. Authorities are investigating the cause of the fire and assessing the safety measures in place at the hospital.
title: Jhansi hospital fire: Another infant dies, toll rises to 12

description: Former Indian coach Ravi Shastri believes India's complacency led to their unexpected home series loss against New Zealand. He emphasizes the importance of a strong start in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy against Australia to regain momentum.
title: 'The most important thing for the coach is...': Shastri on Gambhir's role

description: Indian chess player Bristy Mukherjee won the All India Women Rapid event at the Tata Steel Chess India Festival 2024. During the award ceremony, she touched the feet of chess legend Magnus Carlsen as a sign of respect, surprising him. Carlsen also emerged victorious in the rapid and blitz categories, solidifying his dominance in the chess world.
title: Viral Video: Carlsen left clueless as Indian female player touches feet

description: In a significant policy shift, President Biden has authorized Ukraine to use US-supplied long-range missiles for strikes inside Russia. This decision, prompted by Russia's deployment of North Korean troops, marks a turning point in US support for Ukraine. While providing a strategic advantage to Kyiv, the move has sparked criticism, with some accusing Biden of escalating the conflict.
title: 'Trying to start WW-III': Biden ups the ante against Putin ... and Trump

description: The GST Council is gearing up for a pivotal meeting on December 21st, where a decision on the GST rate for health and life insurance will take center stage. The Council is also considering proposals to increase GST on higher-priced footwear and wristwatches, potentially raising rates from 18% to 28%.
title: GST Council to decide on GST rate for health, life insurance on Dec 21

description: The Indian cricket team, including Virat Kohli, Sarfaraz Khan, and Mohammed Siraj, recently had a fun photoshoot, highlighting their strong team spirit before the Border-Gavaskar Trophy.  The team is deep in preparation for the series against Australia, with the first Test starting on November 22nd.  Both teams are ready for an exciting competition in this significant Test series.
title: Watch: Sarfaraz Khan, Mohammed Siraj sum up Virat Kohli in one word during Border-Gavaskar Trophy photoshoot

description: At the CNBC Global Leadership Summit, Infosys co-founder Narayana Murthy reignited debates on work-life balance, championing a 70-hour workweek as essential for India’s economic rise. While his stance echoes the nation's entrenched overwork culture, critics argue for reforms to counter rising burnout rates. The article explores whether relentless work or balanced well-being is the key to productivity and sustained growth.
title: Is life-work equilibrium an elusive ideal or essential for productivity?

description: Seven Indian fishermen were rescued by the Indian Coast Guard after being apprehended by a Pakistan Maritime Security Agency ship near the India-Pakistan Maritime Boundary. The fishermen were retrieved safely, but their fishing boat, Kal Bhairav, was damaged and sunk. A joint investigation is underway to determine the circumstances leading to the incident.
title: 'A 2-hr chase, a daring rescue': ICG ship intercepts Pak maritime vessel, saves 7 fishermen

description: China is experiencing a surge in violent attacks, including a recent stabbing at a vocational college that left eight dead and a car ramming incident that killed 35. These incidents, attributed to economic pressures and social anxieties, challenge China's image as a safe nation and highlight growing discontent amidst an economic slowdown and limited opportunities for young people.
title: Car rampage, stabbing: What's driving mass killings in China

description: Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) chairman Mohsin Naqvi asserted that the Champions Trophy will be held in Pakistan as scheduled, dismissing any possibility of a hybrid model.  Naqvi urged India to communicate any concerns directly to the PCB for resolution. He emphasized Pakistan's commitment to hosting the tournament while urging the ICC to prioritize its credibility by swiftly announcing the schedule.
title: CT will be held in Pakistan, no hybrid model: PCB

description: A priest in Hyderabad sustained injuries from a minor explosion that transpired near a temple on Monday. The incident occurred while the priest was clearing garbage outside the temple. Authorities swiftly responded, securing the area and transporting the injured priest to a hospital where his condition is reported as stable.
title: Explosion near temple in Hyderabad, priest hurt; probe under way

description: Indian Defence Minister Rajnath Singh is slated to meet his Chinese counterpart, Dong Jun, during the ASEAN Defence Ministers’ Meeting Plus in Laos. This potential meeting, the first since 2020 border clashes, signals a step towards improved diplomatic relations as the two nations recently concluded military disengagement in eastern Ladakh.
title: Rajnath may hold bilateral meet with Chinese counterpart in Laos: Govt

description: The Supreme Court has directed all NCR states to strictly implement GRAP Stage 4 pollution control measures, regardless of AQI fluctuations. The court mandated the formation of monitoring teams, establishment of grievance redressal mechanisms, and consideration of stopping physical classes. This decision comes as the court criticizes the Delhi government's delayed response and emphasizes citizens' right to a clean environment.
title: Delhi pollution: SC gives strict orders to NCR states on curbs, schools

description: In a lighthearted Q&A session before the Border-Gavaskar Trophy, KL Rahul playfully named Virat Kohli as the most famous person in his contact list.  Kohli, when asked, reminisced about his memorable century in Perth during the 2018-19 series, a knock met with enthusiastic cries of "Legend!" from teammates Siraj and Sarfaraz.
title: Rahul calls this Indian legend the 'most famous' in his contact list

description: The Reserve Bank of India is launching a pilot program in early 2025 to offer cloud storage services to financial institutions, starting with smaller firms. This initiative, funded by the RBI's asset development fund, aims to provide affordable alternatives to global tech giants and promote data localization.
title: RBI’s plan to take on Google, Amazon & Microsoft with this first-ever service

description: Delhi NCR is experiencing severe air pollution, prompting the implementation of GRAP Stage 4 measures, including traffic restrictions and staggered office hours. The Supreme Court has mandated these measures remain in effect despite fluctuating AQI levels. Meanwhile, Delhi's environment minister criticizes the central government for inaction on stubble burning in neighboring states.
title: AQI level 'severe+'; flights diverted: Delhi pollution crisis top updates

description: Anmol Bishnoi, brother of jailed gangster Lawrence Bishnoi, has been apprehended by California law enforcement. Facing 18 criminal cases and a ₹10 lakh reward from the NIA, Anmol is implicated in Baba Siddique's murder, allegedly coordinating logistics and procuring weapons.
title: 'Lawrence Bishnoi's brother Anmol detained in California'

description: The universe is home to many fascinating objects. R Aquarii is a binary star system with a red giant and a white dwarf. Omega Centauri is a globular cluster with millions of stars. M87 is a galaxy with a supermassive black hole. NGC 5253 is a starburst galaxy with intense star formation. NGC 1672 is a barred spiral galaxy.
title: Hubble space telescope: A glimpse into the latest stunning space images

description: JK Rowling criticized John Oliver for his stance on transgender athletes in women's sports, calling his arguments "absolute bullshit."  Rowling cited a UN report claiming female athletes have lost numerous medals to transgender competitors and alleged girls have been removed from teams to accommodate transgender athletes.
title: 'I liked him very much when I met him but ... ': JK Rowling slams John Oliver

description: A 77-year-old retired engineer from Rohini, Delhi, fell victim to a sophisticated "digital arrest" scam, losing Rs 10.3 crore over 19 days. The scammers, impersonating courier company representatives, police, and ED officers, manipulated the victim into believing he was implicated in a parcel scam. They coerced him into transferring funds to avoid legal trouble, maintaining control through threats and intimidation.
title: Parcel scam: How an engineer lost Rs 10 cr to Digital Arrest that went on for 19 days

description: Rahul Gandhi, leader of the opposition, accused PM Modi of lying about his stance on reservation. Gandhi stated that the INDIA bloc aims to increase reservation quotas. He promised to raise ST, SC, and OBC reservations. Gandhi criticized BJP for allegedly favoring capitalists. Jharkhand and Maharashtra held assembly elections. Vote counting is scheduled for November 23.
title: 'PM Modi lying': Rahul Gandhi says INDIA bloc to break 50% quota cap

description: Vijay Wadettiwar, Congress leader, dismisses dissent within the Mahayuti alliance as theatrics and highlights farmer distress, inflation, and the BJP's divisive politics as key election issues. He frames the Maharashtra assembly polls as a battle of ideologies between the Constitution and the RSS, emphasizing the MVA's commitment to social justice and economic well-being.
title: BJP can't dent MVA prospects in Maharashtra polls: Wadettiwar

description: Daksh Gupta, founder of Greptile, sparked controversy after revealing his company's intense work culture on social media.  His post, detailing 12-hour workdays and weekend shifts, elicited both support and criticism, including death threats.
title: US-based AI startup's Indian-origin CEO on getting death threats: I started telling candidates...

description: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath, during a Jharkhand rally, hinted at pursuing the construction of a Krishna temple in Mathura after the Ram Mandir inauguration. He heavily criticized the ruling JMM-led coalition, accusing them of corruption, illegal mining, and fostering infiltration. Adityanath pledged to recover looted funds, provide jobs, and expel infiltrators if the NDA comes to power.
title: 'Time for Krishna Temple in Mathura': UP CM Adityanath in J'khand

description: Mitchell Starc's record-breaking INR 24.75 crore acquisition by Kolkata Knight Riders in the IPL 2024 auction might be short-lived. Former cricketer Irfan Pathan predicts Rishabh Pant could surpass this figure in the upcoming IPL 2025 mega auction. Pant's recent return to form and exceptional abilities have fueled speculation of a record-breaking bid.
title: Irfan picks new most expensive player ahead of IPL auction

description: The Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) retaliated against Rahul Gandhi's "ek hai toh safe hai" jab, labeling him "Chota Popat" and accusing the Gandhi family of looting India's treasury.
title: 'Chotta popat': BJP hits back at Rahul Gandhi over his'safe' jibe

description: Due to dense fog and severe air pollution in Delhi, eleven flights were diverted, and numerous others faced delays at Delhi's Indira Gandhi International Airport.  The diversions, primarily to Jaipur and one to Dehradun, were necessary as some pilots lacked the required training for low-visibility landings. Despite the challenging conditions, flight operations are currently proceeding as scheduled.
title: Delhi pollution: 11 flights diverted, many delayed as dense fog hits air traffic

description: Neuroscientist Kelly Lambert and her team at the University of Richmond discovered that rats not only can learn to drive small vehicles but also exhibit genuine enjoyment in the process. The rats, trained using Froot Loops as rewards, displayed excitement and anticipation before driving sessions, suggesting a positive emotional response to operating the vehicles.
title: Mini cars, big thrills: Forget cheese, rats have need for speed

description: Jake Paul emerged victorious against Mike Tyson in a lacklustre match. Following the bout, Mike Tyson challenged Logan Paul to a match. Jake Paul challenged Conor McGregor to an MMA fight. McGregor has not yet responded to the challenge. Mike Tyson's challenge to Logan Paul suggests he is not ready to retire.
title: After Mike Tyson, Jake Paul wants to fight Connor McGregor

description: Apollo, a stray dog living at the Giza Pyramids, became an overnight sensation after a video of him scaling the Great Pyramid of Khafre went viral. His newfound fame has not only boosted local tourism but also brought attention to the plight of stray animals in Egypt.
title: Apollo, the stray dog scaling Egypt’s pyramids, becomes viral sensation

description: Parkinson's disease cases will rise to 3.15 million by 2033.  The increase will be seen in seven countries including the US, UK and Japan.  Older adults are most affected by this brain disorder.  The disease impacts movement, mental health and sleep.  Treatment can help manage symptoms but the disease remains a concern for aging populations.
title: Parkinson’s disease to surge to 3.15 million worldwide by 2033, finds report

description: The Delhi High Court has granted a temporary reprieve to former cricketer Gautam Gambhir by halting a lower court's decision to reinstate charges against him in a real estate fraud case. Gambhir, currently the head coach of the Indian cricket team, had previously been cleared of wrongdoing by a magistrate's court.
title: Delhi HC stays discharge order for Gautam Gambhir in cheating case

description: As Delhi faces hazardous air quality, Ayurveda offers practical solutions for respiratory health. From turmeric milk's soothing properties to amla juice's immunity boost, these remedies, alongside oil pulling and neem water hygiene, provide natural defenses against pollution. Anulom Vilom breathing further strengthens the lungs, promoting overall well-being amidst challenging air conditions.
title: 5 practical Ayurvedic tips to help you stay healthy in Delhi’s polluted air

description: Nishant Jaiswal, a silk artisan and aspiring IPS officer, appeared on Kaun Banega Crorepati 16, sharing his inspiring journey.  His story of determination, including walking to Amitabh Bachchan's house with a wish to be on the show, resonated with the host. Mr. Bachchan shared his own early struggles, creating a heartwarming moment of shared aspirations and perseverance.
title: KBC 16: Amitabh Bachchan reflects on his transformation from struggle to success

description: Former India pacer Dodda Ganesh believes that fast-tracking rookie Nitish Kumar Reddy for the Border Gavaskar Trophy serves no purpose. Despite impressive performances in the IPL and T20Is, Ganesh argues that Reddy is still undercooked for Test cricket and suggests opting for a specialist bowler or batter instead in the playing eleven for the first Test beginning November 22 in Perth.
title: 'Fast-tracking Nitish Reddy for Tests serves no purpose'

description: Amit Shah and PM Modi have praised the film Sabarmati Report. The film revisits the Godhra train burning incident and its aftermath.  The film stars Vikrant Massey, Raashii Khanna, and Ridhi Dogra.  It was released on Friday.  The Sabarmati Report is based on true events.  The film aims to uncover the truth of the controversial incident.
title: 'Exposes truth': After PM Modi, Amit Shah backs 'Sabarmati Report'

description: In a thrilling Test match in Adelaide in 2003, Ajit Agarkar's remarkable spell of 6 wickets for 41 runs against Australia proved decisive in India's historic victory. Agarkar's dismissals of key Australian batsmen, including Langer, Ponting, Katich, and Gilchrist, helped restrict Australia to 196 runs, paving the way for India's memorable win.
title: When Agarkar ran through Australia to set up India win in Adelaide

description: Following media scrutiny of its discriminatory hiring practices, Apple supplier Foxconn has directed its Indian recruitment agencies to eliminate age, gender, and marital status requirements from job advertisements for iPhone assembly positions. The company is now promoting workplace benefits instead and has instructed recruiters to remove its name from job postings.
title: Job ad for India's iPhone factory: 'AC, free transport, hostel, and a salary of ….'

description: During a wedding celebration in Rajasthan's Dausa district, a heated argument between a wedding guest and the bride's brother took a dangerous turn. The guest, after a dispute involving celebratory firecrackers, allegedly drove his car into a group of people, leaving nine injured. Seven of the injured are in critical condition.
title: Man runs over 9 with his car after argument at wedding in Rajasthan

description: Despite Virat Kohli's recent struggles in Test cricket, Sunil Gavaskar believes the star batsman will excel in the upcoming series against Australia.
